EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to artificial intelligence; defining “artificial intelligence” in the
context of emergency management; requiring emergency management
plans prepared by the Governor and each plan adopted by a state or
local governmental agency to include provisions ensuring that final
decisions regarding emergency response planning and the allocation of
resources in response to an emergency are not made by artificial
intelligence; prohibiting a public utility from [using artificial
intelligence to make] making a final decision regarding whether to
reduce or [shutdown] shut down utility service in response to a
disaster or emergency [;] based solely on the use of artificial
intelligence; and providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law provides for the development of emergency management plans by state and
2 local governmental agencies. (NRS 414.040) Existing law also authorizes the development of
3 a state emergency management plan. (NRS 414.060) Section 3 of this bill requires such
4 emergency management plans to include certain provisions to ensure final decisions regarding
5 emergency response planning and the allocation of resources in response to an emergency are
6 not made by artificial intelligence.
7 Section 2 of this bill defines “artificial intelligence” in the context of emergency
8 management [.] , and section 4 of this bill applies that definition to the existing provisions
9 of law relating to emergency management.
10 Section 5 of this bill prohibits a public utility from [using artificial intelligence to make]
11 making a final decision regarding whether to reduce or [shutdown] shut down utility service
12 in response to a disaster or emergency [.] based solely on the use of artificial intelligence.

Assembly Amendment No. 200 to Assembly Bill No. 325 Page 4
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 414 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto the
2 provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. “Artificial intelligence” means a machine-based system that can,
4 for a given set of human-defined objectives, make predictions, recommendations
5 or decisions influencing real or virtual environments.
6 Sec. 3. Any state emergency management plan prepared pursuant to NRS
7 414.060 and each plan for emergency operations described in subparagraph (2)
8 of paragraph (b) of subsection 4 of NRS 414.040 that is adopted by a state or
9 local governmental agency must include provisions ensuring that final decisions
10 regarding emergency response planning and the allocation of resources in
11 response to an emergency are not made by artificial intelligence but rather by a
12 natural person.
13 Sec. 4. NRS 414.030 is hereby amended to read as follows:
14 414.030 As used in this chapter, the words and terms defined in NRS 414.031
15 to 414.038, inclusive, and section 2 of this act have the meanings ascribed to them
16 in those sections.
17 Sec. 5. Chapter 704 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
18 section to read as follows:
19 1. A public utility shall not [use artificial intelligence to] make a final
20 decision regarding whether to reduce or [shutdown] shut down utility service in
21 response to a disaster or emergency [.] based solely on the use of artificial
22 intelligence.
23 2. As used in this section:
24 (a) “Artificial intelligence” has the meaning ascribed to it in section 2 of this
25 act.
26 (b) “Disaster” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 414.0335.
27 (c) “Emergency” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS 414.0345.

